# Working with the New S3 bucket UI

A new UI interface was introduced and deployed from February 2025 for S3 buckets in AFID's cloud dashboard. Here are the changes and the new features introduced and the first guide to using them properly. 

### **New S3 Buckets Page**
To view the new interface, login to cloud.afid.io and click on S3 Buckets on the sidebar. Here is a screenshot of the page.

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)

### **Grid Layout**: 
The First change that is apparent is the Grid of boxes layout for listing out the Buckets that the user has access to. This replaces the previous list and also shows more information about the buckets settings like detector and frame strides. Additionally, a group of buttons has been added for file listing (folder icon), edit settings (pen icon), Trigger a rescan of the bucket (refresh icon), delete the existing bucket (trash icon). The exclamation icon denotes error with the bucket configuration. For error message hover or click on the icon. You can hover on each icon to get more details. 

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)

### **Bucket Details Page**:
Clicking on the bucket card or the file icon would open the contents of the bucket.

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)


Here are the components in the bucket detail page.
	
1. The left side of the tree lists the collections in the bucket. Each collection will have a set of video files. 
2. The "green tick" means that the bucket has status Active. In case of error, corresponding status will be visible. 
3. The plus icon button allows users to add a new collection to the bucket. This can be useful for organizing the video files properly in the bucket. 
4. This right section of the browser is the section for displaying the files and their details when one is selected. 
5. The folder/collection can be expanded by clicking on the dropdown icon.
6. The name of the bucket and detector associated is displayed on the top left.

**Selecting a Collection**:

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)
If a folder/collection is selected then the file contents will be listed on the file tree as well as the preview window. 
	
1. List of all video files in the folder
2. File drop zone where the user can click to select the file to be uploaded or drag and drop a video file to upload. Supports only mp4 file uploads.
3. Each video item has a badge with different colors for indicating the state of the processed video. Green means that video is successfully processed. Gray badge means that the video is still being processed. Red badge represents error while processing.
4. The video status or the error message can be viewed by hovering over the top right of the video file in the preview.
5. If the video ran into error during processing, the refresh icon is shown which will reset the video state and send it for reprocessing.
6. Finally the delete icon will delete the video file and its records from both the S3 bucket and the database.

**Selecting a Complete Video**

If a completed video is selected, the preview window will opened as below:
![Image](data:image/png;base64,)
	
1. The selected video file
2. Action button group is at the top for downloading the video file, Downloading the generated emobs file and opening the video item in web streamer.
3. The detection results is the table listing the maxn-frames for each of the detected species. Maxn frame is the frame number in which the detected fish count is maximum for the corresponding species.  
4. The image icon displays the frame image corresponding the the maxn for that species.
5. The Population over time graph is a line graph that shows the time-series data representing how the number of fish detected changes over frames grouped by fish species.
6. The Frame Range selector can be used to crop the selected frame range.

**Inspecting a Failed Video**:
If a failed video is selected instead, the preview will show the error message instead. 

![Image](data:image/png;base64,)
	
1. Error message for what happened. The progress bar displays the percentage of frames scanned successfully.
2. Video Details
3. Selected video file

**Adding a New Bucket**

To Add a new bucket, click on the button at top right "Create bucket"
![Image](data:image/png;base64,)

### **Form Page**:
![Image](data:image/png;base64,)
Here is the documentation for each of the numbered labels in the image:

1. **Bucket Name**  A text input field where the user specifies the name of the S3 bucket.
2. **Model Name**  A dropdown menu for selecting a detection model to be used.
3. **Endpoint URL**  A text input field where users can enter a custom S3 endpoint URL. If using AWS S3, this field can be left blank. A hint below provides an example URL for Pawsey Acacia.
4. **Access Key**  A text input field for entering the S3 access key. This is required for authentication.
5. **Secret Key**  A password input field for entering the S3 secret key. This is masked for security purposes.
6. **Root Directory**  A text input field where the user specifies the root directory inside the bucket. The default value `/` indicates that the entire bucket will be scanned.
7. **Frame Stride**  A numeric input field that determines how frequently frames are processed. A value of `1` means every frame is processed.
8. **Bucket Status**  A text input field displaying the status of the bucket. The value "Active" means only active buckets will be scanned.
9. **Save Button**  A blue button that allows users to save the entered bucket configuration.
10. **Reset Button**  A button that resets the form fields to their default values.
11. **Cancel Button**  A red button that cancels the operation, likely navigating the user away from the form.
